.cli
  %h2 What is it?
  %p
    Gobot CLI is a powerful command line interface tool that provides several tools to make RobotOps and setting up your devices to work with gobot a lot easier.

  %h2 How to install
  %p For the commands to be available everywhere the gobot module needs to be installed globally.

  %p Here's how to do it.

  :markdown
        :::bash
        go get -u github.com/hybridgroup/gobot/gobot

  %p 
    If you need more help to install golang click
    = link_to "here.", "http://golang.org/doc/install", target: "_blank"
  

  %h2 How can I use it?
  %p
    :markdown
      The Gobot CLI tools are easy to use, designed to be intuitive, and offer contextual help regarding the commands you're using. Once you have the `gobot-cli` module installed globally, the toolkit will be available at all times. To find all available commands, just run `gobot help`.

  %h3 Printing a list of available commands
  :markdown
        :::bash
        gobot - 

        Commands:

            generate    Generates a Gobot library skeleton

        Use "gobot help <command>" for more information about a command.

  %h2 What Gobot CLI commands are available?
  %p
    If you have only installed gobot, the list of available commands is the one printed in the section above, let's review them one by one.

  %h3 gobot generate [name]
  %h5 Description
  %p Generates a new Gobot component or adaptor module.
  :markdown
        :::bash
        gobot generate test
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_adaptor.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_driver.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/README.md
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/LICENSE
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_driver_test.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_adaptor_test.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/gobot-test_suite_test.go

  